### Documentation Formatting Rules

#### Markdown Structure
- Use `##` for main sections (Parameters, Returns, Example Usage)
- Use `###` for subsections
- Use `*` for bullet points
- Use `**bold**` for emphasis
- Use `[Link]` for internal documentation links

#### Code Examples
- Always include complete, runnable code examples
- Use descriptive variable names
- Include both basic and advanced usage examples
- Show error handling where appropriate

#### Parameter Documentation
- Include parameter type in description
- Mention default values
- Explain constraints or limitations
- Provide examples of valid values

#### Return Value Documentation
- Clearly state the return type
- Describe what the return value contains
- Mention any special conditions or null cases

#### Exception Documentation
- List all possible exceptions
- Explain what conditions trigger each exception
- Provide guidance on how to handle exceptions

