- All new public APIs must include complete documentation
- Documentation must follow the established format
- Examples must be tested and verified
- Links to related documentation must be valid

#### Automated Checks
- Documentation coverage should be 100% for public APIs
- All code examples should be syntactically correct
- Parameter documentation should include types and defaults
- Return value documentation should be complete

#### Maintenance Schedule
- Review documentation quarterly for accuracy
- Update examples when APIs change
- Remove outdated information
- Add new examples for new features
- Verify all links are still valid

This documentation standard ensures that all code in the WooCommerce Flutter API package is well-documented, consistent, and helpful for developers using the API.
